               <p>WILLIAM DEBENHAM. I am a <rs id="t18170917-253-viclabel1295" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-253-victim1737 t18170917-253-viclabel1295"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-253-victim1739 t18170917-253-viclabel1295"></join>, in partnership with 
               <persName id="t18170917-253-person1740">
                  Thomas 
                  Clark
               <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1740" type="surname" value="Clark"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1740" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1740" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , we live in <placeName id="t18170917-253-crimeloc1296">Wigmore-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-253-crimeloc1296" type="placeName" value="Wigmore-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-253-crimeloc1296" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-253-off1293 t18170917-253-crimeloc1296"></join>. On the 16th of September, about twelve o'clock, I was standing at the door, and saw the prisoner looking at some ribbons on the Counter, and while my young man's back was turned, I saw him put a piece of ribbon into his pocket. I sent for a constable, and desired him to stop him as he came out. He was taken to the watch-house, and nine pieces of ribbon were found on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-253-person1741">DONALD</persName>
             M'DOUGAL. I was serving the prisoner. He asked me for some knee ribbons - I shewed him some; he produced a piece of cloth, and asked me to match that while he matched another. I turned my back, and saw his hand in his pocket, but did not suspect him - He bought 5-8ths of each sort of ribbon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-253-person1742">
                  JAMES 
                  LITTEN
               <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1742" type="surname" value="LITTEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1742" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-253-person1742" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner into custody - He begged forgiveness, and said he would return them. I found 143 yards on him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
